  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This adaptation builds on VDSR's improvements over earlier models like SRCNN by employing a complex training regime enhanced by a higher learning rate and gradient clipping, facilitating more effective learning.",
    "Key to VDSR and by extension, HSCNN is the technique of combining a low-resolution input with the network's output to generate high-resolution images.",
    "However, HSCNN diverges in its application: it repurposes VDSR's super-resolution focused architecture for spectral reconstruction, translating RGB images into detailed hyperspectral outputs.",
    "This strategic modification showcases HSCNN's unique capability to extend a super-resolution framework to the spectral domain, illustrating its specialized application in hyperspectral image reconstruction.",
    "The SR2D/3DNet framework presents two models: one with 2D convolutions for spatial relationships in images and another with 3D convolutions for capturing both spatial and spectral dimensions (Koundinya et al. 2018)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The SR2D/3DNet framework presents two models: one with 2D convolutions for spatial relationships in images and another with 3D convolutions for capturing both spatial and spectral dimensions (Koundinya et al. 2018)."
  ]
